nd global studies. Guiding principles, developed at the East-West Center, include noting uncommon differences, the interplay among Asian societies and traditions, the erosion of authenticity and cultural tradition as an Asian phenomenon as well as a Western one, and the possibilities Asian concepts offer for conceiving culture outside Asian contexts. The work ranges from South to Southeast to East Asia. Essays deal with art, aesthetics, popular culture, religion, geopolitical realities, geography, history, and contemporary times.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aGroup identityzAsia. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Studies. 7aRELIGION / Eastern.2bisacsh1 aAmes, Roger T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAndaya, Barbara Watson, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAndaya, Leonard Y., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAtkins, E. Taylor, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrown, George P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBuck, Elizabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aButler, Lawrence E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChen, Shudong, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDunscomb, Paul E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrissom, Harriette D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHershock, Peter D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJones, David, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLittlejohn, Ronnie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLong, Kelly, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/r